Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Failing test: "should return 60 G for exactly 3 alike components (block discount, 60 + 5 = 65 G)"
Expected behavior: 3 runes should get block discount: 60 G base premium instead of 3 x 25 = 75
Current error: Expected [{ premium: 65 }], Received [{ premium: 80 }]
Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Current implementation in src/claim-office.ts:
```typescript
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
const BASE_PREMIUMS: Record<string, number> = { sword: 100, amulet: 60, staff: 80, potion: 40, rune: 25 };
const basePremium = (item: { type: string }): number => BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type] ?? 0;

interface Customer { yearsWithMHPCO: number; }
interface QuoteResult { premium: number; }

const quotePremium = (items: Array<{ type: string }>): number =>
  items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + basePremium(item), 0) + PROCESSING_FEE;

export const processSteps = (customer: Customer, steps: Array<{ op: string; items: Array<{ type: string }> }>): Array<QuoteResult> =>
  steps.map((step) => ({ premium: quotePremium(step.items) }));
```

Components are types "rune" and "moonstone". A "block" of exactly 3 alike components costs 60 G instead of 3 x 25 = 75 G. The block discount only applies when there are exactly 3 of the same component type.

Need to modify `quotePremium` to detect component blocks. The minimal approach: count component types, if a component type has exactly 3, use 60 instead of 75 for that group.

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

